          <avActivityHighlights>At intermediate and high altitudes a considerable avalanche danger will prevail.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>As a consequence of new snow and wind from southerly directions, avalanche prone wind slabs formed. This applies in particular on steep slopes, as well as in gullies and bowls, and behind abrupt changes in the terrain also at intermediate altitudes. The fresh wind slabs can be released by small loads. &lt;br/&gt; The avalanche prone locations are barely recognisable because of the poor visibility. &lt;br/&gt; Avalanches can be released in deeper layers in particular on steep shady slopes. &lt;br/&gt; Maintaining distances between individuals and one-at-a-time descents are recommended.</avActivityComment>
